#Title#
EpistemeLinks: Philosophy Resources on the Internet
#Content#
Please Note: EpistemeLinks.com is not currently being maintained or updated with new links. EpistemeLinks was started in 1997 and later grew to include over 19,000 categorized links to philosophy resources on the Internet and had several additional features. After becoming increasingly out of date, the site was taken down in 2011. This page now provides selected links to some outstanding resources for philosophy. I hope you find this listing helpful. Â– Thomas Stone Encyclopedias Wikipedia - See the philosophy entry and the philosophy category. Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy Routledge Encyclopedia of Philosophy Encyclopedia Britannica E-Texts and Papers Project Gutenberg - includes numerous classic philosophy texts People with online papers in philosophy - an extensive list maintained by David Chalmers PhilSci Archive - an electronic archive for preprints in the philosophy of science Blogs and Podcasts Philosophical Weblogs - an extensive list maintained by David Chalmers Philosophy Bites - a long-running podcast with interviews of professional, academic philosophers The Philosopher's Zone - a long-running podcast with interviews of professional, academic philosophers Philosophy section at LearnOutLoud.com - the Philosophy section at the podcast directory LearnOutLoud.com Discussion Lists (Listservs) PHILOS-L PHILOSOP Popular Magazines The Philosophers' Magazine Philosophy Now Conferences / Events Conference Alerts - a general site for academic conferences worldwide, see the philosophy section Events in Analytic Philosophy in Europe (and Overseas Countries) Fun and Humor The Philosophical Lexicon Causes of Death of Philosophers Philosophical Humor - a good list of links maintained by David Chalmers Additional Resources Job Search at The Chronicle of Higher Education The Philosophical Gourmet Report - a regularly updated ranking of philosophy graduate programs (and related resources), maintained by Brian Leiter Philosophy Research Index - from the Philosophy Documentation Center International Directory of Philosophy - a subscription-based philosophy database that includes information on thousands of philosophers, university departments, journals, societies and associations, institutes, publishers, etc. Philosophy Pages - a set of excellent, longstanding philosophy resources from Garth Kemerling Fallcy Files - a useful resource on logical fallacies Ethics Updates - a useful set of resources from Lawrence Hinman Please Note: EpistemeLinks.com is not currently being maintained or updated with new links.
